tourBios.curYrHigh: Recorded a top five at the Chitimacha Louisiana Open. After a 69-67 start, fired a third-round 66 and found himself one back after 54 holes. Doubled bogeyed the par-5, 12th hole but pulled within one stroke of the lead after birdies on 14 and 15. Went bogey-par-bogey to end the tournament and settled for a T3.

tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished the Web.com Tour season having played all 25 events. Had three top 10s, six top 25s and made 13 cuts. Was 74th on the combined final money list...Improved each day at the Colombia Championship in February, posting rounds of 70-68-68-67 to claim a T8 finish, his first Tour top-10...Next top 10 didn't come until the Stonebrae Classic, where he birdied the final two holes to snare a T10...See-sawed his way through the summer making a lot of cuts but not contending very often...Picked up his third top 10 at the Price Cutter Charity Championship in August. Highlight of the week in Springfield, Mo. was a third-round 63. A Sunday 69 led to a T10...Four cuts sandwiched around his top 10s in August offset any momentum generated...Played in all 21 events to finish the Regular Season 62nd on the money list...In the Web.com Tour Finals, made one cut (67th at the Nationwide Children's Hospital Championship) in four events.

2014: Finished the PGA TOUR Canada season atop the Order of Merit, with $80,992 in earnings, securing fully exempt status on Web.com Tour for the 2015 season. Captured the PC Financial Open for first PGA TOUR Canada win. Opened with a 6-under 66 and was tied for the 18-hole lead with Mario Clemens and Eugene Wong at the season-opener in Vancouver. Shot a second-round 70 and was three shots behind Wong at the halfway mark. After a third-round 68, came from two shots off the pace Sunday, shooting another 68, to defeat Wong and Brad Clapp by a stroke at Point Grey G&CC...Took the lead at The Syncrude Boreal Open with a first-round, 9-under 63 and never looked back. Finishing with rounds of 66-68-69, five strokes ahead of runner-up Ricky McDonald, became the first wire-to-wire winner on PGA TOUR Canada since John Ellis in 2008... Combined with his win at the PC Financial Open, moved to the top of the Order of Merit...Posted three rounds in the 60s to finish T5 at the Staal Foundation Open for third top-10 finish...Made his second career Web.com Tour appearance when he played in the United Leasing Championship in late-June as a sponsor exemption. Missed the cut in Indiana...As the top player on the Order of Merit through the Staal Foundation Open, earned an exemption into the RBC Canadian Open, where he made his first PGA TOUR start. Went on to finish T53 at Royal Montreal GC...One week later, finished T2 at the ATB Financial Classic for fourth top-10 finish of the season. Finished at 23-under par, with four rounds in the 60s, four strokes behind winner Brock Mackenzie...Missed first cut of the season in ninth start, at The Great Waterway Classic.

2013: Made eight cuts in nine starts, with three top-10s. Shot two rounds of 62, tied for the lowest round on PGA TOUR Canada. Held a share of the 54-hole lead at the Syncrude Boreal Open before finishing T4...Was the 18- and 36-hole leader at the Cape Breton Celtic Classic before finishing seventh...Also was T8 at the Dakota Dunes Open...Was 22nd on Order of Merit. 
2012: Made five cuts in eight starts, including a T3 finish at the Dakota Dunes Open, to end the year 31st on the Order of Merit. 
2011: Returned to PGA TOUR Canada in with a clean bill of health after a testicular cancer diagnosis...Finished with a season-best T4 at the TOUR Championship, where he closed with a final-round 64...Was 55th on Order of Merit. 
2010: Made his first cut, at the Times Colonist Open, and went on to place seventh...Earned exempt status for the season at the Florida Winter Qualifying School...Made his PGA TOUR Canada and pro debut at the Corona Mazatlan Mexican PGA Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Two-time state high school champion in Washington.
tourBios.personal: Was diagnosed with testicular cancer in February 2011 but made a full recovery and returned to PGA TOUR Canada later that season…Biggest thrill outside golf is being a Seattle Seahawks fan…Favorite course played is Clarkston GC…Course he'd most like to play is St. Andrews' Old Course…Never travels without a few books…As a superstition, never marks his ball with a quarter…Favorite pro teams are the Seattle Seahawks and Seattle Mariners. Favorite TV show is "Duck Dynasty," and favorite movie is "Dumb & Dumber." Says his favorite athletes to watch are "All the Seahawks."…Favorite cities to visit are Victoria, British Columbia, and Saskatoon, Saskatchewan…Keeps Clif bars and sunflower seeds in his golf bag as a snack. Dream foursome would include his mom, dad and Dennis Leffler…Not many people know he can "cook a good breakfast."…Personal motto is "Have a lot of fun all the time."…Mother, Jolyn, was a high school basketball player…Lived with PGA TOUR member Nick Taylor for two years after leaving the University of Washington while still remaining in Seattle.
